---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/myBenchNotes-Logo.png';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About this";
	description="My digital logbook";
	pubDate={new Date('>April 11, 2026')}
>
	<div class="wallpaper-bg" style={`background-image: url(${AboutHeroImage.src});`}></div>
	<div class="watermark">UNDER CONSTRUCTION</div>
	<p>
		myBenchNotes is a digital showroom and logbook documenting a life lived at the intersection 
		of strategy, and hardware.
		As an IT Professional with an academic background in Electronics Engineering, I've spent 
		my career managing the "stack".  This site is where I document what happens when those
		technical skills spill over into my personal interests.  Whether I'm troubleshooting a
		defective monitor, optimizing my cycling cadence in the trails around Durham region,
		or calculating a mid-game gambit on the chessboard, everything here follows the same 
		philosophy: <b>Observe, Analyze, and Build</b>.
	</p>

	<p>
		<b>What you'll find here:</b>
			<ul>
				<li><b> The Technical Lab:</b> Documentation of my DIY electronics projects, ESP32 builds, 
						and Home Assistant automations. If there's a circuit to be traced or a script to be
						written, it's here.</li>
				<li><b> The Peloton:</b> Notes from the saddle of my Canyon Ultimate. Expect gear reviews, 
						training data from the ThinkRider, and ride logs from the local routes.</li>
				<li><b> 64 Squares:</b> A space for chess analysis and tournament reflections. A place to
						study the "software" of the mind.</li>
				<li><b> The Atlas:</b> Logs from my travels-capturing the logistics and the stories from 
						road.</li>
			</ul>
				It is a collection of "bench notes" - the raw, iterative process of figuring out how things
				work and how to make them better. 
	</p>
</Layout>
<style>
	/* This creates the seamless wallpaper effect */
	.wallpaper-bg {
		position: fixed;
		top: 50%;
		left: 50%;
		transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
		width: 80vw;
		height: 80vh;
		background-repeat: no-repeat;
		background-position: center;
		background-size: contain;
		opacity: 0.05; /* Very subtle so text is readable */
		z-index: -1; /* Sits behind everything */
		pointer-events: none; /* Allows you to click things "through" the image */
	}

	.content-body {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1; /* Ensures text stays on top */
	}

	.watermark { 
		/* Keeps your diagonal orange text styling */
		z-index: 2;
	}
</style>
